he air engaged and the line as smooth as possible at this very soft dynamic. Keeping the tongue high to keep that air flow fast and consistent (thinking e instead of o) and my corners tight but not squeezing so that I don’t begin to let the pitch suffer. A lot to think about at one time but with time and practice, it will get there! Happy practicing!! 
